      paradigms: ["hormonal_health", "immune_function", "hair_health", "bone_health"],
      description: "Cholecalciferol. Fat-soluble prohormone synthesised in skin upon UVB exposure; converted to 25-OH-D3 (calcidiol) in the liver, then to the active form 1,25-OH2-D3 (calcitriol) in the kidneys and peripheral tissues. Functions as a steroid hormone ligand for the vitamin D receptor (VDR), regulating >1000 genes. Critical for calcium/phosphate homeostasis, immune function, hair follicle cycling, and anti-inflammatory signalling. Deficiency (25-OH-D3 < 20 ng/mL) is widespread and associated with numerous alopecias, autoimmune disease, and metabolic dysfunction.",
